root: ^Hello there, Mr. Tyson, sir. I’ve brought you some piano music.
^Uh, son, this is a toy keyboard.
^And I don’t have no fingers, I can’t play this.
^Well, I c-can try to play a little bit for you?
^[*Fig bashes on the piano, creating an ungodly mash of noise*]
^You know, even though that wasn’t like the old man’s music or, you know, good at all…
^The love in it still felt the same. I think I’m ready to find some new music around the city.
^Now, would you be so kind to tell me about who knows where Broccoli’s at?
^There’s a playground not too far east from here. You’ll find an uppity cat hangin’ around.
^He’s had an accidental run-in or two with Animal Control before, so he’ll know more about where your buddy might be.
^Thank you! You’ve helped me out a dung ton!
